description: TEHRAN – Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian has confirmed that his administration will make use of the expertise of former Foreign Minister Mohammad Javad Zarif as an advisor, highlighting the government's commitment to leveraging the expertise of those who have diligently served the country.
title: Pezeshkian says Zarif will be involved in administration as adviser

description: TEHRAN – In an open parliamentary session on Saturday, President Masoud Pezeshkian emphasized the need for unity and collaboration among the country's three branches of government to effectively address Iran's pressing challenges.
title: Parliament begins review of proposed cabinet as Pezeshkian calls for unity

description: TEHRAN - On August 9, 2024, The Telegraph published an article titled “Iran’s new president battles revolutionary guard to stop all-out war with Israel” by Akhtar Makoii. The following points will discuss the content of this article.
title: The second phase of an assassination

description: TEHRAN – France, Germany, and Britain intend to join the 146 countries recognizing Palestine as a state, contingent upon significant concessions from Iran, including its recognition of Israel and a halt to support for Resistance groups in Palestine, Lebanon, Iraq, and Syria, according to information obtained by the Tehran Times.
title: Exclusive: Europe planning Abraham Accords II

description: TEHRAN- The Iranian ambassador to Armenia engaged in discussions regarding regional developments and the enhancement of bilateral relations with Armenia's deputy prime minister.
title: Iran, Armenia officials discuss expansion of bilateral ties

description: TEHRAN- Iran's acting foreign minister has asserted that the United States plays a role in the crimes committed by the Zionist regime and cannot be viewed as an impartial mediator due to its provision of military support to the regime.
title: ‘United States supporting Zionist crimes in Gaza’: Iran’s FM

description: TEHRAN- The Caspian Media Forum commenced on Saturday in Astrakhan, Russia, with the participation of an Iranian delegation.
title: Iranian delegation attends Caspian Media Forum in Russia

description: TEHRAN – Iranian ambassador to Turkey Mohammad Hassan Habibollahzadeh recently paid a visit to Sincan Prison in Ankara to assess the conditions and well-being of Iranian nationals incarcerated there.
title: Iranian ambassador assesses welfare of inmates jailed in Turkey

description: TEHRAN- Iran’s ambassador to Moscow announced that the President of Russia has formally invited Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian to attend the upcoming BRICS summit in Kazan and sign a Russia-Iran comprehensive agreement.
title: Putin invited Pezeshkian to attend BRICS summit: envoy

description: TEHRAN – The Iranian government has approved and issued a comprehensive directive focused on the organization and security of high-risk centers across the country.
title: Iran approves new directive to enhance security of high-risk centers

description: TEHRAN- The Islamic Republic of Iran Railways has issued a statement affirming its stance against any unauthorized encroachment on its railway territory. This announcement comes in response to the recent intrusion by the private entity known as the "Afghanistan Railway Consortium" into Iranian railway zones.
title: Tehran says no tolerance for encroachment on Iranian railway territory

description: An Israeli airstrike in Gaza killed at least 18 people from same family on Saturday.
title: Israeli airstrike kills 18 members of same family in Gaza Strip

description: The threat of polio is rising fast in the Gaza Strip, prompting aid groups to call for an urgent pause in the war so they can ramp up vaccinations and head off a full-blown outbreak. One case has been confirmed, others are suspected and the virus was detected in wastewater in six different locations in July, AP reported.
title: Aid groups in Gaza aim to avert a polio outbreak

description: A senior British diplomat has resigned from the Foreign Office over the UK’s continued arms sales to Israel, which he said have “no justification”.
title: Senior diplomat resigns over UK’s complicity in ‘war crimes’ in Gaza

description: TEHRAN- A member of the Political Bureau of Hamas in Gaza has underlined that Israeli Prime Minister, Benjamin Netanyahu has deceived the latest round of ceasefire talks in Doha despite efforts by Egyptian and Qatari mediators.
title: Hamas says no progress in Doha talks

description: TEHRAN- Israel has been caught between a rock and a hard place as Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu is making desperate attempts to cover up his army’s failures in the Gaza battlefield.
title: Israel attempting to spin military fiasco as victory over Hamas

description: A senior Hezbollah official said the Lebanese resistance movement’s surprise retaliation for the ongoing Israeli acts of aggression and assassinations of resistance figures in the country will be far beyond the Zionist regime’s imagination.
title: Hezbollah: Retaliation will be beyond Israel’s imagination

description: Hospitals and clinics across India have begun turning away patients except for emergency cases as medical professionals started a 24-hour shutdown on Saturday in protest against the rape and murder of a doctor in the eastern city of Kolkata.
title: Indian doctors go on nationwide strike

description: TEHRAN- “Tótem”, a 2023 movie directed by Mexican film director and screenwriter Lila Avilés, will go on screen at the Andisheh Cultural Center in Tehran on Monday.
title: Andisheh cultural center to review “Tótem”

description: TEHRAN- “The Survivor” soundtrack album composed by the celebrated Iranian musician and composer Majid Entezami has been released about 30 years after the movie was screened.
title: Digital version of “The Survivor” soundtrack album by Majid Entezami released

description: In a cozy and welcoming setting, the toy museum in downtown Tehran offers a fascinating collection of around 1,500 pieces of toys and games.
title: Go back to childhood in toy museum

description: TEHRAN – Belqeys Castle, situated in North Khorasan, is set to receive a significant boost in tourism infrastructure, with new development plans aimed at enhancing the visitor experience.
title: Belqeys Castle to revamp tourism infrastructure

description: TEHRAN - The growing sister-city relationship between Hamedan and Tajikistan’s Kulob is set to drive increased collaboration in trade and tourism, according to the Tajik ambassador to Iran.
title: Hamedan’s heritage fuels partnership with sister-city Kulob

description: TEHRAN - As millions of pilgrims embark on their annual pilgrimage to Iraq’s holy city of Karbala for Arbaeen, the Dehloran region in Ilam province has set up an expanded sales exhibition featuring local handicrafts along the return route.
title: Dehloran hosts handicrafts exhibit for Arbaeen pilgrims

description: TEHRAN - Zanjan, a city steeped in history and tradition, is renowned for its ancient craft of coppersmithing, a tradition that dates back over a thousand years to the Sassanid era.
title: Coppersmithing in Zanjan: a craft with ancient roots and modern challenges

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s handicraft industry has experienced a remarkable 53% increase in exports during the first quarter of this Persian year (started on March 20), compared to the same period last year, signaling strong international demand, a senior official reported.
title: Iranian handicraft shines with 53% export surge in Q1

description: TEHRAN – Iran has taken a significant step towards the potential registration of its historical mosques as a collective property on the UNESCO World Heritage list.
title: Iran considers 34 mosques for potential UNESCO World Heritage label

description: TEHRAN – Iran artistic gymnast Mahdi Olfati continued his historic run at the 2024 Paris Olympics, qualifying for the vault finals. Despite facing numerous challenges, Olfati expressed optimism about securing a medal for Iran at the 2028 Olympics.
title: Mahdi Olfati expresses satisfaction with his performance in 2024 Olympics

description: TEHRAN- The winners of art exhibition "Patterns of Friendship", a joint painting event between Iran and Russia, were celebrated during the opening ceremony, which was held at the Academy of Watercolor and Fine Arts of Sergey Andriyaka in Moscow on Wednesday.
title: Winners of "Patterns of Friendship" exhibition honored
